# Rovr — Deployment, Chroma, and Production Ops

**Before any deploy:** complete `.cursor/rules/railway-pre-deploy-checklist.mdc`. Cross-IDE copy: `AGENTS.md`.

## Architecture (code vs index)

- **Git push / `railway up`** updates application code; triggers S3 restore only when local Chroma is empty (~3 min cold start).
- **Chroma index** source of truth: S3 `s3://experienceleaguechatbot/chroma_db/chroma_db.tar.gz` (~41k chunks).
- **Runtime persist path:** fresh `/tmp/chroma_data_*` per container (see `backend/main.py` `_restore_chroma_from_s3`). Do **not** rely on `/app/chroma_db` or `/tmp/chroma_db`.
- **GHA** (`refresh-docs.yml`) updates S3 incrementally; Railway does not auto-sync unless index empty or `FORCE_CHROMA_RESTORE=true`.
- **Never upload local Chroma to S3** without verifying chunk count matches or exceeds production.

